Boundary Conditions and Deformations: General Remarks 

The  supersymmetric  vector model in the boundary
has been studied extensively in the 
literature using mainly a -model approach. It
possesses two critical points at large-, one free and one interacting, which have
various supersymmetric and non-supersymmetric
deformations that could be considered. We consider several such deformations in Section , although the 
"double-trace" deformations of the supersymmetric fixed points are of particular interest.
From the bulk point of view,
these correspond to suitable choices of the boundary conditions for
scalars and spinors. We review this  in the present context below.

Scalars 

